entry.title: camera: Pass internal screen's rotation angle to VCD delegate directly
entry.content:
Currently ScreenObserverDelegate pass a reference of Display to VCD

delegate when screen's event happens. However, it is not safe to pass

reference if we can't control its lifetime. In this case, copy a Display

object and pass it to the task runner is much safer. Moreover, since VCD

delegate only need screen's rotation angle, this CL only passed the

angle to task runner.

entry.title: [Desktop] Avoid logging PopupItemId::kSeePromoCodeDetails.
entry.content:
If PopupItemId::kSeePromoCodeDetails is handled inside the AED,

the Chrome will crash. This happens because AED calls

BAM::OnSingleFieldSuggestionSelected, which calls

GetEventTypeFromSingleFieldSuggestionPopupItemId. The last function

crashes if it receives PopupItemId::kSeePromoCodeDetails.



This CL makes BAM::OnSingleFieldSuggestionSelected not handle this

popup item id. The AED unit tests are modified so that they test how

AED handles this popup item id.

entry.title: Refactor blind_sign_auth_proto to use proto deps
entry.content:
Some context: A proto_library works by generating two different targets, let's call the main target "A"



"A" is a static library that will depend on the output of an action. This action is called "A_gen" which takes protobuf

files and generate cpp files.



When we add an entry to `deps` in a `proto_library`, this dependency is added twice, once for target "A"

and another for target "A_gen". Adding it twice is redundant in this case because it is not desirable to

link `anonymous_tokens_cc_proto` because it is being pulled from another path as seen below also this

follows the structure that is recommended by crbug/938011.



//net:net_unittests --[private]-->

//net:net_unittests__library --[private]-->

//third_party/anonymous_tokens:anonymous_tokens_tests --[private]-->

//third_party/anonymous_tokens:anonymous_tokens_pb_openssl_converters --[public]-->

//third_party/anonymous_tokens:anonymous_tokens_cc_proto



In an ideal world, there should be a way to only depend on a fileset that includes

the proto files instead of depending on an action that transforms proto file to cpp files but

unfortunately, GN does not have any support for fileset.



Using `import_dirs` is unrecommended in Chromium because it circumvents proto checkdeps which lead

to using dependencies that might be there due to sheer luck.



Bug: 938011

entry.title: [mullet m3] Suggestion generator has suggestions for unclassified fields
entry.content:
Part of Mullet M3 project, we want users to be able to trigger autofill

from the context menu on unclassified fields or on fields which are

classified as something different than an address.



This CL assumes it is possible to trigger autofill on such fields from

the context menu (this part of the feature will be implemented in a

future CL, as it needs the functionality from this CL).



This assumption implies that

AutofillSuggestionGenerator::GetSuggestionsForProfiles is called with

the following arguments:



triggering_field_type = UKNOWN_TYPE or non-address type

trigger_source = kManualFallbackAddress



The main text and the label of the suggestions are chosen in the same

way they are chosen in the autofill settings page.

entry.title: [Autofill] Fix AreCollapsible() for [Trigger]FillFieldLogEvent
entry.content:
Before this CL, a necessary condition for [Trigger]FillFieldLogEvent

being collapsible was that they have *distinct* `field_event_id`s.



Some observations:

1. Every TriggerFillFieldLogEvent is always followed by a

FillFieldLogEvent, so it's never collapsed.

2. Any two consecutive FillFieldLogEvent have distinct

`field_event_id`s. According to the current logic, they would

be collapsed, provided they also satisfy the other necessary

conditions, such as equality of `was_autofilled`.

3. The above only applies for BAM::FillOrPreviewDataModelForm().

The single-field-filling events seem to be broken anyway

(crbug.com/1508698).



This CL flips the necessary condition to requiring *identical*

`field_event_id`s. By the above observations,

- this is irrelevant for TriggerFillFieldLogEvents;

- this leads to less collapsing of FillFieldLogEvents.

entry.title: Fix ProfileTokenQuality CHECK() failure
entry.content:
Each ProfileTokenQuality object is associated with an AutofillProfile

and responsible for collecting observations for that profile.

Observations are only collected for supported types of that profile,

as enforced by a CHECK() in AddObservation().



Similarly, observations can only be queried through

GetObservationTypesForFieldType(field_type) for `field_type`s that the

profile supports. This is enforced by a CHECK() too.



Turns out that both of these CHECK()s can fail. This CL fixes this.



The first CHECK(), testing that the type of the submitted field is

supported, was supposed to be implied by the following if:

field.autofill_source_profile_guid() == profile_->guid()

I.e, if the field was filled with the profile, the field's type must be

among the supported types. This is wrong for several reasons:

1. The form might dynamically change and the type observed at submission

time can be different from the type observed at filling time.

2. Before submission, a user might change the country of their profile

(e.g. in settings). Since the set of supported types depends on the

country of the profile, this can break the CHECK().

3. With granular filling of unclassified fields, it's possible to fill

fields with UNKNOWN_TYPE.



1 is fixed by instead of looking at the type of the field at submission,

using the recently introduced (b/311604770) AutofillField::

autofilled_type(), which represents the type of the information that

was filled. In most cases, this is just the field's overall type.



2 is fixed by checking that the autofilled_type() is still supported.



3 should in theory be fixed by 1, but this is an open Mullet TODO.



For the GetObservationTypesForFieldType(), the CHECK() is currently only

violated by metrics code [1] that relies on the same

autofill_source_profile_guid() if. It could be fixed by using

autofilled_type() as well, but this CL instead removes the CHECK() in

GetObservationTypesForFieldType().

The rationale is that, as described above, there are a few subtleties

around supported types. It is thus likely that future applications of

ProfileTokenQuality (e.g. the voting mechanism) will run into similar

problems. Instead of failing a CHECK(), just returning an empty set of

observations in this case seems more robust.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:components/autofill/core/browser/metrics/profile_token_quality_metrics.cc;l=147-161;drc=8e78783dc1f7007bad46d657c9f332614e240fd8



Fixed: 1509899

entry.title: [Blink] DrawingBuffer: Set ColorSpace after creating SI
entry.content:
With Mappable SI, DrawingBuffer won't have the ability to set the

ColorSpace on the IOSurface until after the SharedImage has been

created. This CL makes that ordering flip in advance to smooth the port.



Reasoning from ccameron@ on why the ordering of the two calls doesn't

matter here:



"The reason for the SetColorSpace() call is that CoreAnimation uses the

IOSurface's color space, while viz uses the SharedImage's color space.

Ideally they should be the same.



If we call CreateSharedImage with a GMB, then we assume that the

IOSurface is having its color space set somewhere else, and we don't set

it [on the service side]. This introduces the possibility that the

IOSurface and the SharedImage might have different color spaces, which

was the bug that resulted in that call being made.



With that background: The order shouldn't matter at all, rather, all

that matters is that both the IOSurface and the SharedImage are

eventually set to have the same color space."



Bug: 1431497

app publishers creating until it's ready, after reading from the

is downloaded.

collect more data and avoid the crash.

entry.title: Only collect app regions for Window Controls Overlay & Borderless apps
entry.content:
This change improves performance for sites that use the CSS property

`app-region` by choosing to not collect the draggable and

non-draggable regions defined by this property when the site is opened

in a normal browser tab since a normal browser tab does not make use

of draggable/non-draggable regions.



By default, `LocalFrame::SupportsAppRegion()` is `false`, and it is

only set to `true` for PWA windows with either Borderless or Window

Controls Overlay enabled.



To support app regions in PWA windows, we check

`AppBrowserController::OnTabInserted/Removed` to handle the case where

web content is reparented into or out of an app window.



To support deprecated Chrome Apps (which are supported on ChromeOS

until Jan 2025), set SupportsAppRegion to true for frameless apps

in `NativeAppWindowViews::RenderFrameCreated`.

entry.content:
Speculative fix (will monitor test reviver). This does not repro on any

device I own nor on any emulators (including those on CI/CQ).



What appears to be happening is multiple copies of the Incognito card

are being displayed. One suspect for this is batching causing reset to

be delayed. Another is a lingering static variables for whether the

message card was shown. Fix this by both unbatching the test and

resetting the static value.



This same fix may apply to TabGridIphTest.



Also use onViewWaiting in the event the message cards are delayed.



This will likely pass CQ because we don't have any arm builders on

CQ that run chrome_public_test_apk only on CI :/
